    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-11-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-11-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="578" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d578">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Dayton.</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 434.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-11-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 25, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have received your despatch of October
                            29, (No. 371,) which gives an account of the entrance of the pirate
                            Georgia into Cherbourg, and of your proceedings therein. The President’s
                            views of these events have been made known in a previous
                            communication.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William</hi> L. <hi rend="smallcaps">Dayton</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c.,
                                &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
